parameters:
Emma, a member of the thief gang, said, What should we do in
reality? I've been starting to remember words lately...

Captain Clevo: No matter where they escape within the
empire, they're all the same, those beastmen. They're just
prey for the nobles.

Emma, a member of the thief gang, said, Why don't we just
sell them off to the nobles--

Captain Clevo: I don't consider that a joke. We, who have
been robbed, will not take away this person's life.

Emma, a member of the thief gang, said, I-I'm sorry...
Captain.

Captain Clevo: I think it's essential to train this person
as a thief and teach them how to protect themselves.

Captain Clevo: Aside from their abilities as a thief, I felt
that they possess considerable strength and natural
intuition.

Emma, a member of the thief gang, said, I've already broken
about five plates, but do you think I might be more suited
for a warrior or something rather than a thief?
Captain Clevo: I agree with that.

Chef Sid: Hey, even though difficult conversations are fine,
you gotta eat!

Chef Sid: Don't worry, I have your portion too. It's
fulfilling as a chef to see you enjoy it so deliciously.

Chef Sid: Hey, how about we decide on a name for our captain
soon?

Emma, a member of the thief gang, said, Certainly, it's
pitiful for someone like you or a beastman.
Captain Clevo: I understand... Then, let's go with Nora.

Chef Sid: Ahaha, you're an amazing person, but sometimes
you're like that.

Captain Clevo: S-Shut up! Hey, Nora! From today, your name
is Nora!

Chef Sid: Ahaha, Nora loves bread so much. The first word
she learned was 'bread,' so I win.

Names are mysterious things. By being given a name, an
'existence' begins to take shape. In fact, Nora underwent a
significant change from the day she was named 'Nora'.

Like dry sand absorbing water, she learned words and her
beast-like behavior gradually disappeared. At the same time,
a sense of fear towards men and an inferiority complex of
not being able to acquire thief skills shaped her
personality.

The reason Clevo and the others didn't have a problem with
Nora's personality was not only because they thought they
couldn't do anything about it themselves, but also because
they ultimately intended to make her leave the Emma Thief
Gang.

The Emma Thief Gang is a group that aims to reclaim the land
that was taken from the nobles, and Nora has no connection
to them. They believed that it would increase Nora's chances
of survival if she remained timid rather than being
aggressive.

However, Nora stubbornly refused to leave the Emma Thief
Gang. It was simply because Nora loved the members of the
Emma Thief Gang.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Emma, a member of the thief gang: It's clear that the
security of the entire campus has become stricter. There are
even guards patrolling not only the city, but also the
grasslands.

Captain Clevo: It was expected... Once the post-war
processing is complete, the guards will return.

Captain Clevo: Of course, it is only natural to mobilize our
troops to crush those disgusting scum of the Loparo plunder
gang who have been increasing their influence.

Emma, a member of the thief gang: We still have supplies...
but if things continue like this, we will definitely be
under siege.

Emma, a member of the thief gang: As ordered, we have
secured a new route. There is a possibility that we won't be
able to buy and sell within the campus anymore.

Chef Sid: If only I had the eyes of a dragon, I could turn
the tables in an instant.

Chef Sid: Don't you know? The eyes of the magical beast
dragon are said to be as beautiful as gemstones.

Chef Sid: They say that a single pair of eyes is worth
enough to buy a city.

Captain Clevo: Dragons don't exist. What we should be
thinking about is reality, not fantasy.

Chef Sid: It's just a little joke. I'll try to come up with
ways to be creative with my cooking and save on ingredients.
Captain Clevo: ...Did you hear any noise just now?
Chef Sid: Is that so? You should take a little break too.
Chef Sid: At times like this, I should bake some bread...

Chef Sid: I mentioned the name of the bread, but Nora isn't
coming.

Clevo and the others noticed Nora's disappearance several
hours after Sid noticed it.

By this time, Nora herself had started calling herself a
thief and defined herself as a member of the Emma Thief
Guild.

I had received a favor and wanted to contribute to the Emma
Thief Guild in any way possible. However, I began to think
that it would be difficult to repay the favor in that field
due to my low skills as a thief.

The information about the 'Dragon's Eyes' that I heard at
that time. If we have them, perhaps we can make the dream of
reclaiming the stolen land, which is the long-cherished
desire of the Emma Thief Guild, a reality rather than a
fantasy.

Nora had impulsively left the hideout. It was all for the
sake of the Emma Thief Guild, for the sake of her comrades,
and for the sake of the person who gave her a [name].
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
